**Segments**

- **By Technology**: The LTE and 5G broadcast market can be segmented by technology into LTE Broadcast and 5G Broadcast. LTE Broadcast is the existing technology that enables the delivery of broadcast/multicast services with the one-to-many broadcast mode in LTE networks. On the other hand, 5G Broadcast, which is a new advancement, leverages the capabilities of 5G networks to provide more efficient and enhanced broadcast services.

- **By End-Use**: Another way to segment this market is by end-use, which includes video-on-demand, mobile TV, connected cars, emergency alerts, stadium venues, e-newspapers & e-magazines, fixed LTE quadruple play, radio, data feeds & notifications, content delivery network, and others. Each segment has unique requirements and utilization of LTE and 5G broadcast services based on the specific needs of the end-users.

